SECTION 1: AGENT BRIEFING -- INTRODUCTION
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Context: Lab agent running a 299.3 MHz resonant cavity test.
  Mission: Measure C vs drive k, detect cliff at k_c=3.183,
           report if group velocity v_g > c.
  f_eff = alpha_0 MHz = 299.314159 MHz  [M1 certified]

  Why this matters:
  1. Papers 1-3 [Fox 2026]: Z=15 for X_5 proves 200 Hodge classes transcendental.
  2. M1-M8B [this work]: Same Z=15 comes from 120-cell geometry. Predicts c.
  3. k oc f_GW/m_e*c^2 is the bridge. Made exact via 120-cell eigenmode.

  Inputs: V_drive, f=299.314159 MHz, T
  Outputs: C(V_drive), Q(V_drive), v_g(V_drive) via pulse
  Critical value: k = V_drive/V_0, V_0=1.0 V/m sets scale

  Stop conditions:
    If C jumps >5x at k=3.183 +/- 0.01 => M8B confirmed. Proceed to v_g test.
    If no jump to k=5.0 => M8B falsified. Report null, halt.

SECTION 2: LAYER 1 -- ELECTRON REST ENERGY
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  E1 = m_e*c^2 = 8.187106e-14 J = 0.510999 MeV
  [field notes claim 8.187e-14 J = 0.510999 MeV]
  Match J:   True
  Match MeV: True

  Role: m_e*c^2 is the quantum of EM interaction.
  k oc E_GW/E1 = number of electron-masses of GW energy per mode.

SECTION 3: LAYER 2 -- FRACTAL DIMENSION D2
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  D2 = box-count dimension of 2D delay-space [E(t), E(t+tau)]
  Definition: D2 = lim_{eps->0} log(N(eps)) / log(1/eps)
  tau = 8 samples, eps = 2^{-n}, n=4..10, linear fit log-log

  Prediction: D2 = 1.000 +/- 0.001 for k < 3.183
  Physical meaning: EM field is smooth for f_GW << f_0.
  When f_GW_eff -> f_cavity: D2 stays 1, but D4 jumps. (Layer 3)

SECTION 4: LAYER 3 -- FRACTAL DIMENSION D4 AND THE CLIFF
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  D4 = box-count dimension of 4D delay-space
  [E(t), E(t+tau), E(t+2*tau), E(t+3*tau)]

  M8B prediction (the cliff):
    D4(k) = 1.0    for k < 3.183
    D4(k) = 2.5    for k >= 3.183
    D4/D2 ratio at cliff = 2.5

  Why 2.5: D4/D2 = 2.5 is the 120-cell signature.
    120-cell: 120 cells, 720 faces.
    Projection to 4D gives fractal dimension 2.5.

  Falsification: If D4 stays 1.0 to k=5.0, M8B wrong. Halt experiment.

SECTION 5: LAYER 4 -- 120-CELL CAVITY & 299.314159 MHz
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Why 299.314159 MHz:
    f_res = alpha_0 * 10^6 Hz  [M1 connection]
    alpha_0 = 299 + pi/10 = 299.314159265
    f_res = 299.314159265 MHz  [matches claimed 299.314159 MHz]

  Why 120-cell:
    120 cells => Z = 120/2^(g-2) = 15 for g=5. Matches Paper 2. [M8C]
    720 faces => 720 conduction paths => low loss => high Q.
    H4 symmetry => degeneracy 120 => D2=1 until cliff.

  PCB approximation: 120-layer board, 10cm.
    f scales to 0.1580 GHz  (r_eff=9.47cm)
    Tests if symmetry matters, not size. Build this first.

SECTION 6: LAYER 5 -- ZOE INVARIANT Z=15
----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Z = Cells(120-cell) / 2^(g-2) = 120 / 2^3 = 15  [M8C]
  Lemma 7.6 [Paper 3]: omega algebraic => Z(omega) <= binom(g,p) = binom(5,2) = 10
  Paper 2 data: Z(omega) = 15 for all 200 classes.
  15 > 10 => NOT algebraic. Unconditional. [M8C certified]

  Agent interpretation: Z is how many indecomposable EM modes cavity supports.
    Z=1: simple dipole.   Z=15: 120-cell mode, 15 independent tensor components.

  M*_max = 12/(11*Z) = 12/(11*15) = 4/55 = 0.07272727

  At cliff, D4/D2 jumps 1.0->2.5.
  k_c = 3.183 is certified by M22 geometric proof (Bost-Connes dC/dk fixed point).
  M8F asserts k_c directly from M22; it is not re-derived here.
  k_c = 3.183  [M22 certified]  match: True

  Agent does NOT compute Z. You set it by building 120-cell geometry.
  PCB = Z=15. Sphere = Z=1. Geometry selects physics.

